public interface Cost
extends EffDated
    Cost A delegate representing a unit of price for a period of time that should not be broken up any further. It must be implemented only by an EffDatedBean so that the current cost amount has an effective period.

      • offset

        java.util.List<Transaction> offset(PolicyPeriod branch,
                                   java.util.Set<java.util.Date> transactionDates,
                                   java.math.RoundingMode roundingLevel)
        Refunds the cost in a series of transactions that are subsets of the current amount and period.
        Parameters:
        branch - The branch in which the transactions are created.
        transactionDates - The dates defining the transactions periods. Dates that fall outside of the cost's effective period are ignored. The cost's effective and expiration dates are automatically included when calculating transaction periods. In other worse, an empty, or completely invalid set of dates will result in one offset transaction for the cost's current period and amount.
        roundingLevel - The rounding level to use when prorating the cost's amount to the transaction periods. @see RoundingMode#HALF_UP
        Returns:
        the created transactions

      • onset

        java.util.List<Transaction> onset(PolicyPeriod branch,
                                  java.util.Set<java.util.Date> transactionDates,
                                  java.math.RoundingMode roundingLevel)
        Charges the cost in a series of transactions that are subsets of the current amount and period.
        Parameters:
        branch - The branch in which the transactions are created.
        transactionDates - The dates defining the transactions periods. Dates that fall outside of the cost's effective period are ignored. The cost's effective and expiration dates are automatically included when calculating transaction periods. In other worse, an empty, or completely invalid set of dates will result in one onset transaction for the cost's current period and amount.
        roundingLevel - The rounding level to use when prorating the cost's amount to the transaction periods. RoundingMode#HALF_UP
        Returns:
        the created transactions

      • removeFromTerm

        void removeFromTerm()
        Remove a cost entirely from the term. This is different from the normal EffDated.remove() mechanics that normally truncate the cost to the slice date. This method removes and never persists a cost if it has not been persisted. If it has already been persisted, then it sets ExpirationDate to the EffectiveDate so that it has 0 days of effectivity.
